iples are to be discovered." This one-volume edition presents the essence of the other side of that crucial dialogue. It can be read as a genuine counterpart to the Federalist Papers; as an original source companion to Storing's brilliant essay What the Anti-Federalists Were For (volume I of The Complete Anti-Federalist, available as a separate paperback); or as a guide to exploring the full range of Anti-Federalist writing. The Anti-Federalist makes a fundamental source of our political heritage accessible to everyone.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh1 aDry, Murray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDry, Murray.1 aStoring, Herbert J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package Archive 1960-1989z978311066784440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226775623423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226775623.jpg  a978-3-11-066784-4  UChP eBook-Package Archive 1960-1989c1960d1989  aGBV-deGruyter-alles